# Import Rules

## Absolute Imports

All imports in the project must use absolute paths instead of relative paths. This makes the code more maintainable and easier to refactor.

### ✅ Correct:
```dart
import 'package:app/data/dto/profile_dto.dart';
```

### ❌ Incorrect:
```dart
import '../dto/profile_dto.dart';
import './profile_dto.dart';
```

This rule applies to all Dart files in the project. Using absolute imports makes the code more predictable and helps avoid confusion with nested relative paths.
